title: Arizona Rock 'n' Roll Bike Tour
description: Recreational, non-timed fun ride to precede the 2014 Rock n Roll Arizona Marathon

title: UA Bio Park Wednesday Night Speed
Team El Paso Training Camp with Gord Fraser
description:
Gord Fraser is one of the most successful North American Professional Cyclists who raced up until 2006. A native of Ottawa Canada, Fraser spent many off-seasons training in Tucson which he now calls home. He rode track with the Canadian National Team and enjoyed over 200 wins in his professional career including some top 20 finishes in the 1997 Tour de France. 
He runs his own coaching company in Arizona (www.gordfrasercoaching.com) on top of being Director Sportif of the Canadian National Road Team, and last year co-directing with Frankie Andreu at Kenda 5-hour Energy Pro Cycling continental squad. 
Fraser is our guest and will be instructing our clinic giving several presentations including climbing, sprinting (his specialty), and various aspects of training for the upcoming season This is definitely a once in a life time opportunity that you don't want to miss out on!
course: Friday is a traveling day for everyone to drive up to Tucson and get settled. We will have dinner together that night and get to know everyone. Saturday, Gord Fraser will begin with a lecture followed by a ride approximately 80-90 miles, on flat terrain focusing on pace lines, breakaway strategies, and rotation in the peloton. Saturday evening we will go to a planned dinner with a presentation by Gord on recovery and other aspects. Sunday morning we will begin with a presentation on climbing and descending, followed by the final ride, climbing up Mt. Lemmon. A roughly 21-mile climb.

title: 16th Annual Colossal Cave Road Race
description: Arizona's largest one day road race, continues for its 16th year.  Colossol Cave Road Race will offer the same great venue and same great competition.
course: A beautiful 9 mile circuit of rolling terrain on Tucson's east side. Course is a clockwise loop of Colossal Cave Road (freshly widened), Camino Loma Alta, Old Spanish Trail, and Pistol Hill. Feed zone located on Old Spanish Trail at the Pistol Hill intersection. Finish is near the top of the the Pistol Hill climb.
registration:
Registration will be available at www.arizonareg.com
Prices increase Midnight, April 1
Online registration closes April 9,
On-site registration will be available until 30 minutes before event
notes: Race will be held rain or shine. Helmets are required. Promoter reserves the right to combine or eliminate categories or change payouts dependent on field sizes. Yellow line rule will be enforced. No parking in the feed zone! Riders finish on the same lap as category winner. Dropped Riders may be pulled. Wheel support will be wheels-in/wheels-out.
directions:
In Tucson: Take Old Spanish Trail past the Rincon Store about 2 miles turn RIGHT on Camino Loma Alta (traveling opposite the way the race goes) to Colossal Cave Road then make a LEFT turn (heading EAST). Parking will be about 2 miles after the turn. THERE WILL NO CARS ALLOWED ON PISTOL HILL ROAD FROM OLD SPANISH TRAIL. This is for safety & less congestion.

From Phoenix: Take I-10 east to Exit 279 (Vail/Wentworth) Go North 6.5 miles. You will cross a set of railroad track and have to make a right turn at a light just pass the new Walgreen’s. At the top of the hill stay to the right (you will be on Colossal Cave Road) as you pass Camino Loma Alta. After Camino Loma Alta the parking will be about 2 miles past

PLEASE PARK OFF THE ROAD WAY ON THE EAST OR RIGHT SIDE OF THE ROAD AS YOU ENTER, AS WE WILL BE RACING USING THE WEST SIDE OF THE ROADWAY!!!!!!!!!!

title: Sierra Vista Foray at the Fort
Spring Grand Prix
description: A criterium event in Avondale, AZ
course: A .7 mile course with 3 90 degree corners and a long sweeping right hand turn to the finish.
registration: Both online and onsite registration accepted.  Late fee applies after 4/23/2014 of $10.
notes:
We apologize about the shortened race times.  The City of Avondale is opening the library at 1pm on Sunday, thus we had to finish at 1pm to make this work.  This is the exception, not the norm for our races.

Registration is between City Hall and the Library. Junior categories will have male and females scored separate.
directions:
Take I-10 west from the downtown Phoenix area.  Exit Avondale Blvd and head south.  Turn left on Coldwater Springs, or Jefferson to race parking.   
Enter City of Avondale: 11465 W Civic Center Dr., Avondale, AZ 85323 for GPS directions
